## Detection Built on Three Layers of Intelligence

|||||||| combines multiple detection approaches so security teams are not dependent on a constant stream of manual reviews to stay protected.

### 1. Policy-Driven Detection

Define requirements and define what normal looks like for your environment.

Administrators set policies based on operational requirements, such as geographic restrictions or required endpoint protections. From that initial point, |||||||| continuously evaluates activity against those expectations and generates tickets when something falls outside the defined behavior.

### 2. Best-Practice Detection

Security expertise is applied by default.

|||||||| identifies common risk conditions using established security patterns, including suspicious email infrastructure, known malicious signatures, and other widely recognized indicators of compromise, even when no custom rules are configured.

### 3. Behavior-Based Detection

Detection which adjusts as the environment changes.

Instead of relying only on fixed rules, |||||||| analyzes user and system behavior to surface patterns that are not immediately obvious. This includes anomalies in access patterns, unusual activity timing, and deviations from typical user behavior that may indicate risk.

---

## Automated Response, Human Oversight When Required

In most cases, |||||||| can resolve detected issues automatically. Tickets are remediated and closed without requiring manual intervention.

When additional context is needed, tickets remain open and are surfaced in the management console for review. Administrators can investigate, take action, and close out the issue directly.

> **Note**
> In detection-only configurations, tickets are automatically closed after a defined time period to maintain a clean operational view.

---

## Full Transparency and Audit Readiness

Every detection and response is recorded. |||||||| maintains a complete history of security activity, including automated actions and administrator decisions.

This provides:

- End-to-end visibility into security events  
- Clear audit trails for compliance requirements  
- Traceability for every response and resolution  

